    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-20T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-20T13:00:00-05:00" n="564"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d564">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/5–2054: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States Delegation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-20T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 20, 1954—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 268. Repeated information Bangkok 8,
                    Paris 309, Saigon 99, <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>/NY 1. <persName
                        corresp="#p_RWS1">Robertson</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_PH1"
                        >Phleger</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BPW1">Bonsal</persName> today
                    discussed with Prince <persName corresp="#p_WWKNB1">Wan</persName> question
                    Thailand initiating United Nations <gloss target="#t_POC1">POC</gloss> action.
                        <persName corresp="#p_RWS1">Robertson</persName> gave Prince <persName
                        corresp="#p_WWKNB1">Wan</persName> gist of second paragraph <gloss
                        target="#t_Tosec1">Tosec</gloss> 203<note n="1" xml:id="d564fn1">Dated May
                        19, <ref target="#pg_851">p. 851</ref>.</note> and read him <persName
                        corresp="#p_LHCJ1">Lodge</persName>’s comments contained New York’s 745 to
                    Department, repeated information to Geneva as 2.<note n="2" xml:id="d564fn2">Not
                        printed, but see <ref target="#pg_862">footnote 2, p. 862</ref>.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_RWS1">Robertson</persName> also made clear to Prince
                        <persName corresp="#p_WWKNB1">Wan</persName> that French Government now in
                    full agreement this proposal.</p>
                <pb facs="0893" n="867" xml:id="pg_867"/>
                <p>Prince <persName corresp="#p_WWKNB1">Wan</persName> expressed agreement with
                    procedure outlined reference telegram from <persName corresp="#p_LHCJ1"
                        >Lodge</persName>. He is instructing <persName corresp="#p_TK1"
                        >Khoman</persName> to begin drawing up necessary communications and
                    statements and to get in touch with <persName corresp="#p_PH1"
                        >Phleger</persName> and Henkin regarding them. He agrees that Security
                    Council phase should involve Thailand along with support from Cambodia and Laos
                    being introduced only at time of General Assembly consideration. If Department
                    or <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> have further specific suggestions on
                    drafting or procedure, please telegraph them here.</p>
                <p>With regard to timing, <persName corresp="#p_WWKNB1">Wan</persName> still has
                    reservations. He would evidently prefer to await some specific military move
                    upon which Thailand action would be based. We will continue to urge gravity of
                    present situation upon him, desirability of having <gloss target="#t_POC1"
                        >POC</gloss> in place before grave emergency arises and evident intent of
                    Viet Minh to dominate Cambodia and Laos at this time with obvious threat to
                    Thailand.</p>
                <p>Prince <persName corresp="#p_WWKNB1">Wan</persName> particularly impressed by
                    argument that United Nations has been excluded from Indochina situation and that
                    Thailand initiative would be partial remedy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
